trend_summary: Between earliest and latest images, built-up footprint edges outward moderately while the commercial core densifies. New residential cul-de-sacs replace woodland, and the central retail–industrial zone grows with larger white-roof structures. Main arterial roads widen, yet green cover still dominates, preserving a suburban character at medium overall density.
notable_changes: Central retail–industrial precinct gains several large white-roof warehouses.
New housing pockets appear along western and southern edges, replacing tree cover.
Multiple small woodlots cleared for sports fields and parking areas.
Main east-west arterial road widened, with a new interchange or roundabout added.
Vacant lots within existing neighborhoods filled by low-rise residential infill.
